data.description: **Michael Kahnwald** hangs himself and leaves behind a letter that is not to be opened before November 4 at 10:13 PM
**Jonas** passes flyers for the missing boy **Erik Obendorf** on his way to meet his therapist, **Peter Doppler**
Old **Ines** awaits 10:13 PM to open **Michael**'s note
**Ulrich** carries on an affair with **Hannah** during his morning run. He returns to meet his family for breakfast, where **Mikkel** shows off a magic trick

**Jonas** returns to school and discovers **Martha Nielsen** and **Bartosz Tiedemann** are a couple. School principal **Katharina Nielsen** addresses the students about the missing boy **Erik Obendorf**.
At work, **Ulrich** finds the missing boy's parents (**Jürgen** and **Ulla**) complaining to the police chief ****Charlotte** Doppler**. He and **Charlotte** examine tire tracks as leads.
**Regina** finds out that her Hotel is being forced to close due to financial problems
**Ulrich** visits his mother **Jana**, who notes that **Erik**'s case is similar to the dissapearance of her own son **Mads Nielsen** 33 years earlier
**Erik Obendorf** lays in a bunk bed in the 1986 bunker with kids wallpaper and an ominous chair in the middle of the room
**Katharina** finds **Hannah**'s hair on **Ulrich**'s clothing and begins to grow suspicious. **Ulrich** makes plans to meet with **Hannah** again.
**Hannah** arrives at the power plant for a massage appointment with **Alexsander Tiedemann**, the head of the power plant
Old **Helge** escapes from the rest home and interrupts a meeting at the school to tell everyone 'It's going to happen again.'

**Jonas**, **Martha**, **Bartosz**, **Magnus**, **Mikkel** and **Franziska** go to the caves to find Eric's drug stash. They run away when they hear strange noises and their flashlights begin to flicker.
**Jonas** meets a strange man covered in stain oil.
Departure to 1986 via Cave - **Mikkel** goes missing at 10:13pm, taken by **Jonas** to 1986
Departure to 1986 via Cave - **Jonas** takes **Mikkel** through cave to 1986
Old **Ines** reads **Michael**'s Suicide note at 10:13pm
The group realizes that **Mikkel** is missing and informs their parents.
**Ulrich** searches the caves for **Mikkel** but finds nothing
**Peter** calls his wife **Charlotte**, who is with the search party. He struggles to tell her something before she has to go. After hanging up he recites the Serenity Prayer
**Mads** body is found near the caves. **Ulrich** rushes to see it, thinking it might be **Mikkel**
A **hooded figure** straps **Erik** to the chair and places a 1 Pfennig coin on a red string around his neck. The metal eye ring closes.
arrival from ? via ? - **The Stranger** comes to Winden
**Jonas** has a nightmare with oil coming out of his ear. He sees a vision of the man covered in stain oil he saw the previous night
**Charlotte Doppler** speaks with the medical examiner at the autopsy. The **80s boy** has burns around the eyes and his ear canals are destroyed
**Ulrich** searches the caves and finds the welded metal door to the Nuclear Plant
**Magnus Nielsen** confronts **Franziska Doppler** on her walk home through woods. She had overhead everyone plotting to steal the drug stash and joined them at the caves.
**Peter Doppler** cries in his car parked outside the cabin as he listens to the news report about the missing boys - **Erik** and now **Mikkel**

****Tronte** Nielsen** cleans a sweater discreetly while his wife **Jana** calls **Ulrich** to check on him. **Jana** then asks where **Tronte** was the previous night, to which he lies and then leaves to join the search party
**Bartosz** tries calling **Martha**, who doesn't pick up

**Charlotte** tells her team the **80s boy** was found in 80s clothes, with a walkman, and a one-pfennig coin necklace. **Ulrich** tells **Charlotte** about the door he found and requests a search warrant.
**The Stranger** checks in to **Regina**'s hotel with his leather bag apparatus and copy of 'A Journey Through Time'
**Jana Nielsen** replaces the action figures on the grave of her son, **Mads**
**Tronte Nielsen** joins the search party. He remarks cynically that they may or may not find his grandson **Mikkel**
arrival from 1986? via Cave - the **hooded figure** with police tape across cave entrance
**Charlotte** tells **Ulrich** that **Alexsander** has blocked the search warrant. He heads to the power plant to confront **Alexsander**, who denies his request to enter
**Bartosz** finds a phone in **Erik**'s drug stash
**Ulrich** finds **Hannah** waiting for him back at the station. He rejects her advances under the current circumstances.
**Jonas** finds the cave map in **Michael**'s studio

**Ulrich** notices van tire tracks near the scene and remembers that ****Jürgen** Obendorf** (**Erik**'s father) has a van. He goes to the Obendorf junkyard looking for a van but finds drugs and has confrontation with **Jürgen**
**Helge** drags **Erik**'s body on a tarp through the forest
Aleksander orders **Jürgen** move the yellow barrels from the cave to the truck since the Police are now asking questions
**Tronte Nielsen** sneaks out of bed, which his wife **Jana** notices
At midnight the cave makes noises, the lights flicker, and birds fall from the sky
arrival from 2019 via Cave - **Mikkel**

**Mikkel** comes out of the cave alone and goes to Nielsen family home where he sees his father (Teen **Ulrich**) and his mother (Teen **Katharina**). He notices a newspaper on the porch dated November 5th, 1986

**Mikkel** goes inside the Nielsen family house and sees his grandmother **Jana** watching TV, a Raider commercial previously on. She thinks he might know where **Mads** is, but ends up scaring **Mikkel** away
Teen **Charlotte** finds a dead bird while biking through the woods
**Claudia Tiedemann** drives her daughter **Regina** to school
**Mikkel** looks for his mother (the principal ****Katharina** Nielsen**) at school. He runs into young **Hannah** and young **Katharina**.
**Claudia** arrives at work and is greeted by **Helge**, who gives her a gift
Old **Egon** investigates 33 dead sheep. The farmer mentions a new priest at the local church
**Mikkel** goes to the police station looking for his father (police officer **Ulrich Nielsen**). Old **Egon** calls **Ines** over to pick up **Mikkel**.
Reporter **Tronte Nielsen** is waiting for an interview with **Claudia**, with whom he's been having an affair while his son **Mads** is missing.
**Mikkel** is taken to the hospital by by **Ines**
Old **Egon** heads to the Nielsen household to confront **Ulrich**. **Ulrich** calls out Old **Egon** for drinking on the job.
**Claudia** becomes director and confronts Old **Bernd** about the misleading numbers.
Old **Bernd** shows **Claudia** the yellow barrels in the cave
Teen **Charlotte** draws the dead bird in her notebook and reveals that she has a collection of dead birds from recent mass death events
Dr Schaller performs an autopsy and informs Old **Egon** that all 33 sheep have ruptured eardrums
**Regina** comes home to an empty house. She reveals scars from self harming on her forearm.

The lights flicker and birds again begin to fall from the sky. Old **Egon** drives to the dead sheep field at night, but is pelted with falling birds from the sky. Teen **Ulrich** and Teen **Hannah** share a moment at the bus stop

**Mikkel** sees the flickering and escapes back to the cave, hoping to return to 2019. He injures himself in the cave and cries out for help, and then hears **Ulrich** trying to open the metal door in 2019
**Ulrich** heads to the cave to attempt to open the metal door. He hears **Mikkel** cry out for help from the door, across 33 years
**Claudia** unwraps her gift from **Helge** - “A Journey Through Time”
Old **H.G. Tannhaus** works on the time apparatus in his shop
Old **Helge** sits in the nursing home muttering 'Tick-tock'
**Charlotte** and **Peter** wake up in their separate bedrooms, struggling with their marriage. **Franziska** accuses her younger sister **Elisabeth Doppler** of stealing her lipstick.
**Peter** visits Old **Helge** in the nursing home, as he keeps repeating that he 'has to stop him'
**Charlotte** confiscates a wildlife camera while driving **Elisabeth** to school.
**Jonas** explores the caves with map while **The Stranger** spies on him
**Charlotte** meets with the medical examiner looking at the dead bird, and notes that she's seen similar white spots on birds 33 years ago.
**Wöller** informs **Charlotte** that they can't find any of the red dirt near the crime scene. She asks him to pull missing person records going back even further, to 15 years.
**Charlotte** pulls footage from the road the night **Mikkel** dissapeared and sees her husband **Peter**'s car

**Peter** cleans the dirt from his car and receives a call from **Charlotte** wondering why he had called her the night of **Mikkel**'s dissapearance. He lies to her saying that he was working late at the time.
**Magnus** - sitting in on **Franziska**'s class - follows **Franziska** into the woods and sees her take something from the tin under the railroad tie
**Charlotte** asks **Benni** if **Peter** was a client on Monday Nov 4th, **Benni** says **Peter** hasn't been in over a year
**Ulrich** illegally enters Plant to investigate
Old **Helge** overhears that a boy was found with severly burned eyes, as he mutters 'the end is the beginning, and the beginning is the end'
**Jonas** returns to his bike to find a red string on his handle

**Charlotte** drives to the Doppler family cabin where she exam**ines** the dirt, as she begins to suspect **Peter**. The medical examiner calls her to explain the bird also has ruptured eardrums and that there was likey electromagnetic interference that caused the birds to lose direction and fall.
**Charlotte** starts exploring the bunker, but has to leave when she receives a phonecall (about **Ulrich**)
**Magnus** follows **Franziska** back to ballet practice. **Magnus** confronts **Franziska** about the envelope of cash she took from the tin and they have sex in locker room.
**Charlotte** calls **Peter** to ask him to pick up **Elisabeth** and gives him a chance to tell the truth if he's hiding anything
Old **Helge** escapes the nursing home again
arrival from ? via ? - **Noah** to give **Elisabeth** pocket watch
**Elisabeth** walking home alone in the rain, she finds a Raider wrapper and encounters **Noah** in forest
**Ulrich** is caught by Aleksander's security and is banged up as he didn't cooperate. **Charlotte** arrives to pick him up.
**Charlotte** drives **Ulrich** home, but he gets out of the car in frustration
**Charlotte** gets a call from **Peter** indicating that **Elisabeth** is missing. She searches the area and finds **Elisabeth**'s hat
A **hooded figure** goes into the shack
Old **Helge** tells **Wöller** at railroad bridge 'I have to tell him. He has to stop.'
**Elisabeth** arrives back at home encounters and tells **Charlotte** about **Noah** and shows her a pocket watch engraved with 'For **Charlotte**'
**Peter** gets a call from **Wöller** notifying him that he has found **Helge**
**The Stranger** sneaks into Jona's room and marks up the map with 'Follow the signal'
**Helge** grabs the nurse and says he has to stop **Noah**
**Yasin** walking to school by himself in the woods, stops to pick up acorn figure. **Helge** stops him saying 'You must be **Yasin**. **Noah** sent me' and **Helge** kidnaps **Yasin**
**Ulrich** ignores **Hannah**'s calls
**Bartosz** tries calling **Martha**. **Martha** is trying to contact **Jonas**. **Jonas** is concerned where the red string came from.
Winden becomes conerned as yet another boy (**Yasin**) has gone missing
**Charlotte** tells **Elisabeth** **Yasin** went missing and asks her about **Noah**. **Charlotte** confronts **Peter** about is whereabouts on the night Mike went missing
**Ines** gives **Mikkel** a gift, a book I Am Not Afraid
arrival from ? via ? - **Noah** to talk with **Bartosz** via **Erik**'s cell phone
**Bartosz** gets a call from who he thinks is **Erik**'s dealer but its **Noah**, who knew it was **Bartosz** to answer
**Hannah** brings **Katharina** some food, but **Katharina** begins to suspect **Ulrich** and **Hannah**. **Hannah** asks **Ulrich** for a ride back home.

**The Stranger** leaves a package at the front desk with **Regina** to be delivered in the evening to **Jonas Kahnwald**. **The Stranger** will be gone a few days but wants to keep his room for when he returns
**Jonas** and **Bartosz** smoke a bong and play video games talking about **Martha** and a meeting with **Erik**'s dealer
arrival from ? via ? - **Noah** to talk with **Mikkel** at hospital
**Noah**, a priest from St Christopher's Church, visits **Mikkel** at the Hospital where the discuss evolution and the big bang
**Ulrich** breaks affair off with **Hannah**, but she won't let him go
**Katharina** decides she wants to have sex with **Ulrich** and for him to get the condoms as she never wants kids
A social worker informs **Ines** that **Mikkel** will need to be put in a home if his family can't be located. **Ines** mentions she had a son who died shortly after being born.
**Charlotte** explains the 33 year cycle to **Ulrich**, the solar-lunar cycle
**Jonas** meets The Strange at the Church graveyard where he says knew **Jonas**'s father, **Michael Kahnwald**
**Hannah** meets **Mikkel**, the boy from the future, at Hospital as her dad delivers the dry cleaning and they talk magic
Teen **Hannah** sees **Ulrich** and **Katharina** having sex at the high school when her father is delivery dry cleaning
**Martha** performs leading role of the school play Ariadne while **Jonas** watches. He ignores a call from **Bartosz**
departure to 1986 via the Cave - **The Stranger** to talk with Old **H.G. Tannhaus**
**Jonas** and **Martha** kiss backstage
**Bartosz** meets **Noah**, with the Triquetra notebook, in car on the railroad bridge where **Noah** tells him what happens in the next few days
**Charlotte** has a composite sketch of **Noah** produced from his description
**Katharina** asks **Ulrich** if he is cheating on her, and he says he could never do that
Teen **Ulrich** arrested by Old **Egon**, as Teen **Hannah** who falsely accused him of raping Teen **Katharina**
arrival from 2019 via Cave - **The Stranger** to talk with Old H.G Tannhaus
**Jonas** receives package from **The Stranger** with the orb light, Geiger counter, and **Michael**'s suicide note
**Jonas** reads the suicide note and learns that **Michael Kahnwald** is **Mikkel Nielsen**
**Ines** lays the book I Am Not Afraid at **Michael**'s grave site
**Ines** read I Am Not Afraid book to **Mikkel** as he falls asleep at the hospital in room #25. Written in the book it says this book belongs to **Mikkel**.
**The Stranger** goes to the Clockmaker's shop to talk with **H.G. Tannhaus** about time
**Regina** dreams of being tied up to a tree by **Ulrich** and **Katharina** near the cave entrance
The search for the three missing boys - **Erik**, **Mikkel**, and Ysin - continues, with **Charlotte** pushing her team to chase every lead
**Jonas** asks **Hannah** how she met **Michael**
**Ulrich** pulls **Mads** case files from 1986, and listens to **Egon**'s audio cassette where **Jana** says she **Ulrich** and **Tronte** were waiting at home for **Mads** to return
In an act of rebelion, **Martha** and **Magnus** return to school and force **Katharina** to consider that **Mikkel** might be dead
**Regina** learns from her mammography results that she has been diagnosed with breast cancer
**Jonas** discovers the map has been marked up in red ink (by **The Stranger**): 'follow the signa!'
**Ulrich** confronts **Tronte** about **Jana** lying to police that **Tronte** was home the night **Mads** disappeared.
**Jana** tells **Ulrich** he and **Mads** used to fight over the toys and **Mads** cut his chin once.
**Jana** tells him **Tronte** was having an affair (not the first one) with **Claudia** and he was with her that night and **Regina** was the last to see **Mads** alive.
**Magnus** goes under the railroad bridge and opens the tin box he saw **Franziska** open but finds nothing. Then he finds a bird necklace near a mattress with used condoms next to it
**Bartosz** attempts to reconcile with **Martha** backstage before her play. After a failed kiss, she tries to break things off.
**Katharina** discovers from the phone bill that **Ulrich** has been calling **Hannah** quite often
**Jonas** heads to the caves to explore
**Ulrich** goes to the hotel to ask **Regina** about her being the last to see **Mads**. But instead discovers **Hannah** was to one to report the rape in 1986 not **Regina** as he thought
**Katharina** calls into a local radio program to share her theory that a local killer might be responsible for the disappearances.
**Ulrich** confirms from old police records that **Hannah** did indeed report the rape in 1986
Aleksander discovers **Regina** has breast cancer after finding her mammography results. He calls **Regina** to tell her he loves her.
**Ulrich** confronts **Hannah**'s about accusing him of raping **Katharina** back in 1986
**Jonas** finds the red cord and ouroboros and follows the signal with the Geiger counter to the Sic Mundus Creatus Est metal door and passage
**Martha** breaks down during the school play Ariadne talking about death and thinking of **Mikkel** and **Katharina** comforts her. **Bartosz** watches from the audience.
**Jonas** enters the passage and the lights in Winden being to flicker
Old **Tronte** & **Peter** at the shack and bunker check the Triquetra notebook which matches the time **Jonas** left for 1986
**Charlotte** feels the ground shaking outside the plant fence. We also see duct and debris fall within the bunker with **Peter** and Old **Tronte**
**Katharina** attacks **Regina** in front of **Martha** and **Magnus** after the play on the way out of the school because of her comments
**Jonas** takes the right passage where he exits a similar metal door
departure to 1986 via Cave - **Jonas** first time travel at 21:17
**Ulrich** realizes the dead boy found is **Mads** after seeing a photo of him with the same t-shirt they found him in
arrival from 2019 via Cave - **Jonas** first time travel

**Magnus** and **Martha** are bewildered at Kathrina's attack on **Regina** and how you reall ydon't know who your family really is even though you love with them. The bird necklace **Magnus** found earlier lies on the table.
**Jonas** exits the cave and goes to the bus stop where he see missing posters of **Mads**

Teen **Hannah** and her father pull up in the dry cleaning van, they say its late to be walking home alone and he shouldn't be in the rain because of Chernobyl, offering him a ride, but he decl**ines** after realizing it is his mother, **Hannah**
**Ulrich** goes to the morgue and sees the cut on the dead boy's chin and knows it is **Mads**
Old **Helge** dreams of of his young self waking up in the 1986 bunker after touching **Jonas** through the portal. He wakes up in the nursing home and says 'I remember. I remember everything.'
Old **Egon** checks on teen **Ulrich** in the jail cell
**Ulrich** visits **Mads** grave site
Young **Mikkel** sees the Emerald tablet with the triquetra framed on the wall at the hospital
**Jonas** slept overnight in the hunters blind
**Ulrich** goes to ask the pathologist if its possible the body was preserved for 33 years, but she says no

**Jonas** goes to the high school and sees posters of **Mads** missing and speaks with a girl (teen **Regina**) about the date and where he might find **Michael Kahnwald**. She tells him **Ines Kahnwald** works at the hospital

**Egon**'s Police Chief wants him to question plant personnel working the night **Mads** disappeared, but **Egon** wants to investigate if **Ulrich** had something to do with it. **Egon** has 3 months before retirement
As **Charlotte** talks on the phone at Police station about seismic activity, **Wöller** comes in with the approved search warrant for the Plant
Old **Egon** questions **Helge** about **Mads** at Guard Station and sets up interview in 2 days. **Egon** writes 'Why not forest road?' in his day planner
**Ulrich** combs through **Mads** 1986 case file in **Mikkel**'s bedroom where he finds **Egon**'s police day planner but discovers **Helge** was never interviewed.
**Charlotte** executes the search warrant at the Nuclear Power Plant
Old **Egon** stops **Jonas** as he walks down the road in the rain
**Ulrich** calls **Charlotte** to tell him about **Helge** having never been interviewed in 1986, and also note that the night **Yasin** vanished **Helge** was found in the forest.

Old **Egon** gives **Jonas** a lift to the hospital since it is raining along the road and **Jonas** said he hurt his arm. **Egon** asks him if satanism is a thing among teenagers now, **Jonas** laughs and says no
**Charlotte** finds fresh tire tracks, the rope down to the cavern, the welded door, and traces of yellow paint
**Jonas** talks with **Donata Kraus** looking for **Ines**, she says she is with a boy outside
**Ulrich** confronts then attacks Old **Helge** at nursing home, **Helge** recognizes him from 1953 and says 'I can change the past!'
**Jonas** spots **Ines** and **Mikkel** outside the hospital, but **the Stranger** arrives and tells **Jonas** he cannot interfere with **Mikkel**, otherwise he risks erasing his own existence
**Charlotte** suspends **Ulrich** from the case, which she says she should have done on day one
**Helge** gets into his car to leave the Plant and opens the glove box to eat the Raider bar
Old **Egon** interviews **Katharina** and she tells him if anything, she pressured **Ulrich** into having sex. **Egon** doesn't buy it.
**Katharina** tells **Ulrich** she knows about his affair with **Hannah**
**Jonas** sees **Mikkel** and **Hannah** talking near a vending machine, at the hospital, and decides to heed **The Stranger**'s advice as **Hannah** eats a Raider bar

**Ulrich** visits Old **Jana** and she tells him about seeing a man (**Helge**) argue with a priest (**Noah**) in 1986 the day **Mads** disappeared. She saw the same man today, and he had not aged. She knows he was the same man because he had the same ear scarring or disfigurement
departure to 1953 via Cave - **Helge** to get **Yasin**'s body from bunker to sandpile
departure to 1953 via Chair - **Yasin** alive
At the police station, **Wöller** tells **Charlotte** that at least part of the cave system goes under the forest road near the Doppler cabin.

**Charlotte** goes to the cabin and calls **Peter** and asks about **Helge** living in the shack in 1986 and his car accident. **Peter** claims to not know about the cabin since he moved to Winden in 1987, but mentions **Helge**'s accident was on Nov 12, 1986 - three days from today.
**Jonas** heads back to the cave and opens the metal door back to 2019
departure to 2019 via Cave - **Jonas** goes back to 2019 without **Mikkel**
As **Charlotte** is inspecting the the bunker, the lights begin to flicker and the ground shakes in. She finds a scrap of kids wall paper.
The lights begin to flicker and the ground shakes as **Jonas** heads back to 2019 through the cave
Old **Helge** leaves the nursing home to go to the cave
arrival from 1986 via Cave - **Jonas** arrival from 1986 without **Mikkel**
**Jonas** returns home and ask his mom if she believes in fate? Then he burns the suicide note
**Ulrich** returns to the nursing home to find that **Helge** is not there. He does find an acorn stick figure, the book 'A Journey through Time' with a pfennig coin on a red string.
**Ulrich** hears rustling outside and discovers it is **Helge** leaving and follows him. He calls **Charlotte** telling her it is **Helge**, not now but in 1986. They both enter the cave.
departure to 1986 via Cave - Older **Helge** goes to stop his younger self and **Noah**
arrival from 1986 via Chair - **Yasin**'s corpse
arrival from ? via ? - **Noah** to scrub bunker floor
arrival from 1986 via Cave - **Helge** to take **Erik**'s and **Yasin**'s bodies to the construction site sandpile
**Helge** takes **Yasin**'s body out from the bunker on a tarp. **Yasin** has a pfennig coin on a red string around his neck.

In the Bunker, **Noah** is scrubbing the floor with no shirt on and has an Emerald tablet tattoo'ed across most of his back. He writes another date on the wall in chalk: November 9, 1953 underneath an existing one: November 5, 1953. These dates correspond to **Yasin** and **Erik** dying during time travel via the bunker chair
Young **Helge** riding his bike as **Egon** passes him in a Police Volkswagen
**Egon** and his superior **Daniel** look at the bodies of **Yasin** and **Erik** found in a sandpile at Power Plant Construction site as **Helge** looks on
**The Stranger** continues his discussion with **H.G. Tannhaus** about the nature of time and the triquetra
**Ulrich** loses **Helge** in the caves but finds the red string and the ouroboros and follows it to the Sic Mundus creatus Est metal door
departure to 1953 via Cave - **Ulrich** left passage
Young **Helge** is scolded by his mother **Greta** for getting dirty and makes him strip.
**Bernd** comes home and finds out about the bodies from Young **Helge**, then leaves for Police station

The pathologist Udo Meier, tells **Daniel** and **Egon** he has never seen burn marks like the boys have and their ears are destroyed. The also have 1986 coins around their necks, clothes made in China, and one looks Mediterranean or Arabic and the red head has a strange tattoo
arrival from 2019 via Cave - **Ulrich**
Young **Helge** playing at the shack and bunker sees the dates written on the bunker wall.
**H.G. Tannhaus** explains how the cycle repeats every 33 years, and the significance of the number 33
**Egon** and **Daniel** think about the dead boys and discuss the psychology of what makes a murder
Two bullies show up and take his tutor money. **Ulrich** shows up looking for Old **Helge** and tells him next time to bite them.
**H.G. Tannhaus** explains to **The Stranger** how wormholes cause misbehaviors in time: 'Nothing is where it belongs anymore'

**Ulrich** meets his grandmother **Agnes** and his young father young **Tronte** at the crossroads. Anges is looking for **Egon Tiedemann**'s house. **Ulrich** stares at his copy of **H.G. Tannhaus**'s book
**Ulrich** goes the Clockmaker shop, shows him the book asking if the same HG Tannhaus as the author, but he says no. **Ulrich** asks what year is it and he replies with 1953
Young **Claudia** tutors young **Helge** at her house, but he is late and says he forgot the money at home and will bring it next time.
**Agnes** and Young **Tronte** rent room from **Egon** & ****Doris** Tiedemann**. **Doris** asks **Claudia** to show **Tronte** the town later.

Young **Ines** and young **Jana** come to pick up **Daniel Kahnwald**'s watch at the Clockmaker shop. **Ulrich** overhears young **Ines** talking about the boys bodies being found. He goes to the police station, but leaves his coat with his cell phone in the pocket.

**Bernd** holds an investors meeting at the plant construction site as **Daniel Kahnwald** orders the Police to rope off the crime scene. **Bernd** tells **Egon** he thinks it was a coal plant worker conspiracy

Young **Claudia** is showing young **Tronte** around near the cave . Jealous of how she is treating young **Tronte**, **Helge** throws a stick into the cave and **Claudia**'s dog **Gretchen** goes after it and **Helge** runs away
arrival from ? via ? - **Claudia** to get **Gretchen**
departure to 1986 via Cave - **Gretchen** missing, helped by Older **Claudia**

**Ulrich** makes a scene at the Police station wanting to know if one of the boys bodies is his son **Mikkel**. **Egon** describes them but they don't match **Ulrich**'s description of **Mikkel**. **Egon** askes about **Helge Doppler** and **Egon** tells him that **Bernd Doppler** is his father.

**Egon** comes home and is introduced to **Agnes** by **Doris**, and asks why she came to Winden. Anges says her grandmother was from Winden. **Egon** asks what her grandmother's name was, but they are interrupted by young **Claudia** and young **Tronte** returning from the forest where **Gretchen** was lost

**Ulrich** goes to the Doppler Estate and finds young **Helge** on the back steps. **Ulrich** confirms he is ****Helge** Doppler** and shows him the pfennig coin on a red string and asks if he has seen it before. **Helge** says no. **Ulrich** asks about the box and **Helge** shows him the dead birds. **Helge** says he didn't kill them but they are beautiful when dead.
**Ulrich** says **Helge** will kill the boys and his brother **Mads** in the future. **Helge** tries to run but **Ulrich** grabs him. **Helge** bites and kicks **Ulrich** to get away
**Ulrich** chases young **Helge** through the forest and bashes the left side of **Helge**'s head with it. **Ulrich** drags him into the bunker leaving him for dead
**Egon** comes to the Doppler Estate asking after **Gretchen**, but **Greta** is icy towards him and says there is no dog here
**Greta** looking for **Helge** finds his dead bird box on the back steps, but not **Helge**
**Agnes** and **Doris** makeup a bed and brush hands.
**Claudia** sits on the porch waiting for **Gretchen** to return.
